      menu "Hardware"
      
      menu "Power BUS"
         config LUA_RTOS_POWER_BUS_PIN
            int "Power BUS GPIO number"
            range -1 39
            default 27
            help
               Some Lua RTOS compatible boards, such as WHITECAT N2 DEVKIT, have a load switch that can turn on and
               off power rails through a GPIO. In Lua RTOS this feature is know as Power BUS, on which you can connect
               devices that can be turn on and off on-demand, such as sensors and transceivers that are turn off when
               they are not needed to save power consumption.
               
         config LUA_RTOS_POWER_BUS_DELAY
            int "Delay (ms) when Power BUS is turned on"
            default 100
            help
               Load switches need a certain time to stabilize the voltage when they are turned on. This option performs
               a msec delay before the Power BUS is turned on.
      endmenu
         
